How to be a morning person?
Answer:
Wake up when the sun wakes you up.
  
  I started doing that this week and it helps me get up.
  
  Learn to brush your teeth before bed. Don’t eat anything after. It helps when you wake up. Helps to not have your mouth too dry and then do it again when you wake up.
  
  Wash your face riiiight before going to sleep. Then when you wake up maybe have some wet wipes by your bed or a water bottle and a towel or napkin. wet it and wet your mouth, eyes, forehead, nose and neck and ears. Helps me wake up quick!
  
  I get on my phone for a few minutes or watch the news for about 10 minutes. Helps me see something slightly bright 1st thing in the morning and it helps me ear things.
  
  Try talking when you wake up. And yawning and stretching. Makes you feel like you had a great sleep and helps you prepare for morning movement.
  
  Make it cold when you go to sleep. Maybe keep a fan near.. so then when you wake up. You are able to turn it off. Do not have the fan facing towards your face and nose.. this is not good. It can cause you to get stuffy and sick.. ??
  
  When going to sleep, dress in very thin clothing unless you are a very cold person then bundle up! Helps for your comfort!
  
  Add more pillows than usual to your bed for comfort.
  
  Comfortable sheets and blankets are important.
  
  When you wake up. Choose to get dress 1st and brush your teeth and hair and shower/ wash face and look decent to feel more awake. I try to. Helps me wake up in clean clothes and feeling cleaned.
  
  Lastly.. eat something.. maybe something light or a breakfast ? ? item or a rice cake or some sort of a granola bar.
  
  If you don’t have lotta ideas for breakfast items. Look up on Google lists of breakfast items.
  
  Night time preparation to have a good morning ☀️ ? waking up and then morning preparations to having an awesome morning and fantastic day!
  
  If you are working at some sort of a job.. maybe try waking up extra early and maybe try going to sleep a bit early... I’m a gamer and I like my midnight plays.. so the time I lay down is 12:30 and I wake up at 8:30-9
  
  That is about 9 hours of sleep. I like my sleep. You only need 6-8 hours of sleep, but I choose to sleep a bit longer. I wake up and do all this! I feel great! I have dogs too and I try to go out with them and just stand outside for a minute or two. This helps me wake up as well in the morning.

Indian and a little Irish in my family. Mostly Cajun French. But I got that mask during Mardi Gras and the parades down here in Louisiana where I’m from originally. I am not specifying where. I brought it here and it sits on the wall now. Are moved to Mississippi. But umm... we got up in the middle of the night to go to the restroom. On our way back into the room, we started to lay back down. As we started to lay back down, my mask on the wall is quickly lifted, disturbed and then quickly stops moving immediately.
  
  We had a fan on, but it wasn’t pointed towards it and it does move throughout the night slightly, but I have never seen it just jolt and then it stop all the sudden? Immediately.
  
  Newton’s law of motion did not play role in the object continuing its motion. If it has moved or was pushed or was lifted? wouldn’t it have to continue its motion? I’m not no genius.. but I know basic physics. It did not apply here. It was shoved to move and then abruptly stopped. I asked him if he saw that happen? Him a skeptic, said yes.
  
  I said was that normal? He waited a minute and looked at the mask and thought a second and thought the same as me, no.
  
  I have researched the paranormal off and on for the past decade and enjoy the subject and haven’t had a ton of activity happen to me in my life, but that definitely was something.
  
  May I remind you I just moved here. Yeah... true story. I have heard unexplained knocks and sounds throughout the house, but nothing fully bold to say that it’s haunted, no. Hopefully it’s not, cause I sleep here! I am so used to going to the houses, I don’t wanna live in one!
  
  Again.
  
  This is a true story.

  Cabaret is a form of theatrical entertainment featuring music, song, dance, recitation, or drama. It is mainly distinguished by the performance venue, which might be a pub, a restaurant or a nightclub with a stage for performances. The audience, often dining or drinking, does not typically dance but usually sits at tables. Performances are usually introduced by a master of ceremonies or MC. The entertainment, as done by an ensemble of actors and according to its European origins, is often (but not always) oriented towards adult audiences and of a clearly underground nature. Question: Auto correct... I meant “what is love?”
Answer:
It’s okay.

  And some information from the urban dictionary that I agree with I will state bellow.
  
  love ISN'T when you want or need to be with them every second of the day

Question: What does friendship mean to you? What should your friend be like? Do you have a lot of friends? What could be your reasons for discontinuing friendship with a person?
Answer:
This is quite a few questions just saying..
  
  ——————
  
  What does friendship mean to me?
  
  Friendship means a lot to me. My friends mean a lot to me. I feel like friends keep your socializing and positive. I feel like everyone should have some sort of friendship and everyone does whether they realize it or not, whether it be small or large. Whether it be with an animal or human. Friendships are made every single day.
  
  ——
  
  What should my friend be like??
  
  I don’t understand this question?? I mean? my friends are going to be different from any other person’s friends? and your friends? because were all different, ya know?
  
  Unless you’re meaning influential? Friends should be positive, outgoing, trustful, honest, loyal in ways, keep you out of trouble and safe, out of harms way, real, kind to you, at least partially healthy decisions both physically and mentally. Some of these aspects should be in a friend.
  
  ——
  
  Do I have a lot of friends?
  
  I mean I feel like I have a lot of friends. I have people that look up to me. I have people that I look up to. I have lots of actual friends in many different places all over the world. And then I have friends that are right in front of me. I have family from different parts of the world. And then I have family right in front of me. To me I see no difference family and friends are all family. What I am trying to say is I have people that know me worldwide, both friends and family. Honest. So yes. I would say I have quite the bit of friends. Both girls and boys. It’s OK to step out of your comfort zone and explore different cultures and traditions. I feel like that makes you (us) smarter.
  
  ——
  
  What could be my reasons for discontinuing a friendship with a person?
  
  If they are negatively impacting my life or a negative influence? That could be a reason for discontinuing a friendship with that person. I can forgive people but it depends on the level of the decision... you only get one life. There are slight mistakes that could be made, possible regrets, but you only get one life? Is it really worth it? You want to live your life to the fulllist and in a happy healthy way too.
  
  This is a lot of questions but I guess I see why you asked them all together because they are related.
  
  Hopefully I can answer the questions well enough for ya.

Question: What is the secret to a happy life? ?®
Answer:
Be positive.
  
  Live a little.
  
  Go out and socialize.
  
  Do things that you wouldn’t. But do them accordingly. Think smart.
  
  Seek some sort of education throughout your life. Be successful with that some sort of education.
  
  Make close relationships with your friends and family. Go out and have fun with friends and family. Take road trips. Express your favorite hobbies and talents with them.
  
  Explore nature alone.
  
  Then explore nature with people.
  
  Maybe meditate or exercise occasionally.
  
  Eat a moderately healthy diet.
  
  Care for people.
  
  Help other people even when not asked.
  
  Do for others even if they don’t do for you.
  
  Volunteer work.
  
  Buy something for someone random that you know. Tell them you don’t want nothing in return.
  
  Buy something for someone you don’t know.
  
  Then tell them you don’t want anything back in return.
  
  Do random kind gestures.
  
  Be a lady or gentleman in life.
  
  Get you a regular job and work your ass off. Go buy something that doesn’t make sense with that money that you worked your ass off for. (Don’t do this all the time.) Enjoy that item. Appreciate that item. Live life. I feel like these are the keys to happiness.

Question: Tell me about your flaws ?
Answer:
Me, I try to be pretty honest about my flaws. I have quite a few.
  
  I like to talk a lot. Some people think that that is annoying but honestly I don’t think people know what they want? In this world ?? Because sometimes I don’t talk a lot and they get mad when I don’t talk more? It doesn’t really make any sense. I guess you can’t please everyone and anyone honestly. But that’s one of my flaws.
  
  Besides my real bad reading disorders and anxiety problems. I have problems with my eyes  adjusting to different lighting‘s. Say I went from going inside to outside and it’s really dark for my eyes it would take longer for them to adjust than the normal eye. Considering I’ve never been checked by a doctor on this I don’t know if this is normal or not? But I feel like it’s not. Can’t see that well at night or in the dark at all. Sometimes my eyes adjust and sometimes they don’t at all. So therefore that means I can’t really drive at night. Sucks.
  
  I do get really aggravated easily. Trying to work on that I just have really bad pet peeves.
  
  I have really bad compulsive OCD. Meaning my anxiety leads to repetitive overactive routines and really aggravated compulsions.
  
  I don’t really like it when people touch me. I like things very neat and clean. If I see something out of order, I have to fix it. Not like big things, just like if a room is a little messy, I have to try to tidy it up a bit. If I don’t do it, then I tend to get really upset and little anxiety comes in.
  
  I mean it’s not like I am psycho and trying to kill people? I just have some anxiety that needs releasing and I release it through cleaning. It makes me feel good when I complete something. So I try to be really determined about things. That’s a good thing.
  
  —-
  
  ... So really bad cleaning problems. Organization freak.
  
  Quite a bit of phobias. Claustrophobia. Touch phobia. Have bad driving phobia.
  
  Get easily aggravated. That’s pet peeve’s, but don’t we all have them?
  
  Talk a lot & have moments when I stay mute. Times when I don’t talk enough and times that I do not talk enough. Lol XD this one keeps me confused still. I think this is just human? What do I know? Lol.
  
  Overactive compulsion disorder OCD I have dealt with this for over 10 years.
  
  A lot of anxiety from having really bad reading problems as a kid. Was bullied a lot for my disabilities. Got special treatment in school because I really did struggle with ?. reading and comprehension. People thought it was unfair. But I wasn’t passing because of the disability was alway holding me down... I worked hard every day... I studied. I wasn’t a bad kid. I paid attention in school. I took tons of notes ?.
  
  But this being also known as Dyslexia. I was slightly diagnosed in the first grade with it and then again in the 8th. They were for sure I had it. It’s a struggle throughout my day today life. There isn’t anything I can’t not do. I still try my best to complete things that are a little more challenging. Still human. We all have flaws.

Question: What’s the nicest thing a complete stranger has done for you or vice versa?
Answer: I paid for this ladies groceries that was not fully English and didn’t understand that she owed me more money. But that was okay.. I could understand her a little and she could understand me a little.. but not much. So I just paid for it for her stuff, she didn’t have enough. She had kids with her and all she had was groceries to feed them. So I was like why not? I didn’t have much to give, but I knew she needed a hand. She then noticed after what I did and was surprised. I still don’t know if she understood what happened or what I was saying, but I think she caught on when she saw me swipe my card. A few months later, maybe a few weeks or so, she came back and bought me a dozen of roses. I didn’t want anything in return but I didn’t know she already bought and paid for them. She gave them to me and thanked me over and over again. She said, “You help me out, so that is for you. “ (something like that she said) It warmed my heart.. That was the nicest thing anyone’s ever done for me that I didn’t know at all. That was a stranger. ♥️

Question: How can you change the World?
Answer:
Do you mean as a whole? The world? I’m trying to think... is this some sort of a category or something? I’m trying to think of a way to answer this question. There’s just so many ways you could answer this question. I do not know if I will answer it in the right way your asking.

  Honestly, you can do any action and it change the world whether it’s good  or not.
  
  But environmentally, emotionally, socially, politically, physically, mentally, traditionally, culturally... etc.. we can change the world.
  
  All of that can result in a worldly change. It’s just up to people to choose to do it and in a positive way.
  
  *Me* as an individual *I* myself feel like I have in some ways, may have changed the world. Everyday I try to be kind and as helpful as possible.
  
  I treat people the way that they would treat me. If people choose to do something very nice for me obviously I’m going to say thank you and try to return the kind act. Be realistic, and remain trustful at the same time. Not hurt or be offensive.
  
  I try to help elderly people, the blind and deaf. I have penpals from all over the world and some that speak many different languages. I still try to translate and talk to them no matter what kind of barrier is in the way. I try to keep them company. I know American sign language in Spanish. (Language for the deaf and Spainish) I know a tad bit of Spanish sign language. I know some forms of braille. (Language for the blind) any other language I know how to translate from their native language to English. I try to let them feel more comfortable talking to me then me talking to them. When talking to them I let them speak their native language and then I figure out what they’re trying to talk to me about. Non-stress conversation for them.. I try to make it.
  
  I used to volunteer at a food pantry that my grandmother and grandfather were in charge of and would help feed some of the poorly living people down here in Louisiana sometime hurricane victims. I did that on and off for years and years, probably over 10 years? Yeah. About.
  
  I research the paranormal heavily. Occasionally I get people that need help with certain things going on in their life in this area and I try my best to openly help them as much as I can. Freely.
  
  I work at a convenience store and try to openly help people with anything they need in the area. Tourists that sometimes need answers. Just try to be as convenient as I can about things.
  
  Enough about me!! I know this question is about how I can change the world. But honestly every day each one of us wake up and decide to do something in a day it’s changing the world. Question: Don't give up. I believe in you. Keep fighting. You're gonna make it through
Answer:
Why... all I have done is cared about each and every fucking person around me... to go through and stand right next to them to make sure they didn’t have to go through whatever it is alone.
  
  NOT ONCE has anyone done that for me. NOT ONCE has someone offered me help when it was obvious I was hurting. THERE HAS ONLY BEEN ONE PERSON who has noticed that something was wrong or bothering me. It was my producer and she gave me a cupcake with an m&m smile on it. I fucking cried. Because as little of a gesture it was. It was the fact the she was the only person to ever notice, and she was the only one to actually say/do something nice.
  
  But since then, that was 2013 mind you... and since there has one other person asked to see if I’m alright, is everything alright. Not one person who’ was ever there evenwhen they said they’would be.. no one had kept there. So why?!
  
  Why should I keep continuing with trying to help others who either don’t want it or don’t care to notice it.
  
  When can I just give up on everyone and finally just focus on my self. Because every single time I help someone to be in a better place, I always end up being the one who’s gets broken into pieces because of the weight of the situation.
  
  I’m tired. I’m so fucking tired.  I so sad and depressed for so goddamn long and no one noticed or no one put a hand out to help me for sinking in my depression. Until I met someone who unknown their knowledge took it all away. And when they left without a word, I was crushed like I was back to the beginning.
  
  I don’t ask anyone to take some of my burdens, or ask them to do things for me, I ask for nothing!
  
  I legit feel dead inside at times bc of that feeling.
  
  Do you know what that’s like?!
  
  To be the one who’d do any and everything for someone, take help take a burden to always be there for a friend or a loved one... just so they have a chance at being happy, yet no one is willing to do that for you?
  
  It’s fucking soul crushing. I’m fucking breaking down just writing this because I don’t have any one I can just talk to about this. Just random fucking people who are asking me me random questions ... I might as well answer them on here.  It’s not going to change the situation at all. No ones gonna hear them; no one is going to read them.
  
  So trust me when I say, “yes. I keep fighting... I just don’t know if I should anymore....”
  
  The joyful and happy life that I want in life doesn’t want me,
  
  and doesn’t want my help...
  
  What do you say to someone who feels that way....
  
  Do they keep fighting?
  
  After all they’ve been through, who’s gonna be there for them when THEY NEED IT......
  
  what do they have to fight for? what? . more people who don’t give a fuck about them?

Question: What’s something everyone should do at least once in their life?
Answer:
Disconnect.
  
  When you disconnect; you get another perspective on what life is like without all the gadgets, without Internet, and especially without social media.
  
  You get a chance to to see what’s in front of you. You give your senses the ability to focus on things most people normally miss. you get a sense of what nature like is like, even if it’s from your balcony or window.
  
  You start appreciating everything that goes around you.
  
  I do it all the time, though I shouldn’t, ha. But you start to really to get an  appreciation for anything, everything and everyone around. You see life as it is. Well it’s like that for me. I don’t know if it’s like this for everybody else. I don’t take for granted and come to appreciate the value each and every moment we spend not only just being alive. But spending those moments around those we love.
  
  I might’ve gotten a little deeper this one but that’s just my perspective. Everybody should disconnect every now and then, to appreciate what’s in front of you.

Question: Why do people choose to miscommunicate instead of hearing others out and listening to their side of the story? It’s crazy to me how some people would rather start drama and then blame you for it...
Answer:
Well that sort of all depends on the context of the situation at hand. You have to look at it from both perspectives. And take into consideration to how each side she’s it from their perspective.
  
  •Is the miscommunication happening from one end and not the other.
  
  •Is it happening because of both sides?
  
  •Are they both to blame?
  
  •What has caused led up to hem not wanting to hear out or listen?
  
  •Are they even giving the other side a chance to hear them out?
  
  •How does the other side see things?
  
  •Perhaps they’ve waited and wanted to hear them out; but were never given the chance?
  
  •What if they just got so tired of waiting?
  
  •What if they chose to rant so they can put something out there expressing their frustration for being forced to wait, and the other side not falling through with that was said.
  
  •What if ranting was the only way to get out what they wanted to say because it might either catch the other sides attention?
  
  What it that was their only way to get across that frustration because they haven’t been getting any sort of response at all.
  
  There are assortment of questions that should be asked as well as answered before anyone make the assumptions that those are just some out-of-pocket rants/ means to start drama, or to say they’re putting blame on someone else.

Question: yeah but I'm a bum that's ready to work, they literally just sit and choose names
Answer:
I think there’s a lot more to it than just that, ha.
  
  If I was hiring someone, I’d look at the resume first.
  
  To look and see the way it’s formatted as well the way it’s structured, how much you say, how much you don’t say.
  
  It all depends on how much valuable detail you provide, and how much you don’t.
  
  Also depends on your job experience; I’d look at the job experience between each candidate to see who would work best. Who has the right attitude, and compare and contrast them to see who’d be the best pick for the company out of the bunch.
  
  Also I’d look at your references.  I’d check with the provided references to see what made them hire you, and what made you leave.
  
  You can learn a lot about someone just through their resume.
